cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the development of an energy-efficient digital signature scheme for resource-limited embedded devices, particularly in the medical domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper discusses the need for scalable authentication and dispute resolution in IoT applications involving sensitive data. The paper also proposes a novel signature scheme that achieves near-optimal signer efficiency, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the security of the proposed scheme, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
